CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Don your cherry red stripes and white polka dots to rouse the crowd.

Description.LocalizedString: Santa has gifts for all of you, whether you've been good…or bad.
Even in the 17th century, clowns were bright and colorful.
His classic tailcoat burst open as his stomach inflated, tearing the flesh of his bulging belly.
The blood from a previous adventure is still soaked into the adorable pink fabric. Fun!
A body formed of gluttony and carnage, with armor that barely contains him.
It’s the old ‘fat man in a little coat’ joke, but the punchline here is that he slashes your belly and cuts out your spleen. Admittedly, it’s never gotten many laughs from the audience.
No one even took notice of the stretched state of his costume, completely unaware that he should not be trusted with anything, let alone the young and gullible.
You’ve got your stripes, solids, and polka-dots, paired with an offensive number of gaudy colors and patches. No problems here.
When asked what kind of pattern he wanted for this costume, his answer was simply, “yes.”

A hand-stitched lapel tailcoat that carries deceitful devices.
A classic tailcoat with button-up shirt pushed far beyond its stretching point.

A classic, colorful clown costume with ruffled collar. Scare kids and grown-ups alike!

Description.LocalizedString: Hey you! Pull my finger…
A classic, colorful clown costume with a bloodstained, ruffled collar.
Show your victim how happy you are to see them with this costume.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A dressy doll hat to adorn the hair you have stapled on for this unique performance.

Description.LocalizedString: A dressy doll hat to match the dark stripes covering his face for a unique performance. Who could mistake that face lurking in the dark?
Who could mistake that face? The white beard, the funny red nose and cloth cap. It has to be Santa, right?
A grotesque face, carved out of wood and worn by age. So weathered that it almost looks like skin.
He carved a smile on his face that oozed with putrid matter.
A silly elephant face that’s sure to bring a smile to the next disemboweled victim. Their insides feel warm and slimy, yay!
Fearsome horns sprout from Jeffrey’s head and a golden mask, as grisly as his true visage, adorns him.
It was a lot of work tracking down a killer in his territory and he was getting surly. Enough with the gags, it was time to inflict some pain.
He smiled and promised chocolate to the kids, so they came rushing in. He still had it.
The height of clown fashion, balanced precariously on a clownish head.
The sunburn left when wearing this hat was very strange.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: As above, so below. As below, so above.
As above, so below. As below, so above.

Description.LocalizedString: A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Sometimes, one requires a mask to hide the anguish and torment within.

Description.LocalizedString: Turn your distress and tears into jest, your pain and sobbing into a funny face.
Sometimes, one requires a mask to hide the anguish and torment within.
Behind the mask was a bitter, angry face demanding blood.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A rusty folding pocket knife with a hand-carved rosewood handle.

Description.LocalizedString: Santa receives a lot of mail, so his letter opener needs to be long and very, very sharp. Would you like to see it?
Theater knives generally have blades that retract into the handle, to protect the performers. This one doesn't.
A rudimentary stone knife injected with serum to inflict pain in stomach-churning style.
This special blade is Mr. Puddles’ best buddy. It’s the power of friendship!
A diabolically sharp blade depicting the three-headed hellhound, it encourages its wielder to draw in close and make the battle personal.
A thin-bladed knife made for gutting fish. Requires a bit of strength but allows for a much more personal feeling when cutting through sinew.
This special blade may seem polished and refined, but when used triggers some terrible, agonizing, screams.
A versatile knife that can be used to carve up pumpkins or people.
A handy razor for shaving that also works for slicing necks. Kind of a two-in-one deal.
A old-fashioned straight razor, perfect for putting up against necks.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: An oversized switchblade, as accustomed to inflicting torture and pain as it is to removing limbs and appendages.
An oversized switchblade, as accustomed to inflicting torture and pain as it is to removing limbs and appendages.
A large, foldable straight razor, used for more than just providing close shaves.
